gomodel:SYNGO_4987  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6c,d: Immunogold EM imaging of mouse cerebellum showed particles for Cbln3 were exclusively detected in the synaptic cleft between parallel fiber synaptic terminals.. Experimental description: M&M: \"For production of a polyclonal antibody to Cbln3, cDNA fragment, which is preceded with a BamHI site and encodes 41-74 amino acid residues (NM198114; putative cerebellin-3 peptide for 59-74 and its preceding sequence for 41-58), was obtained by PCR. After the TA cloning using a pGEM-T Easy Vector System I kit (Promega, Madison, WI, USA), cDNA fragments were sequenced and excised by BamHI and EcoRI. These fragments were subcloned into Bam- HI / EcoRI site of pGEX4T-2 plasmid (GE Healthcare Bio-Sciences) for expression of glutathione S-transferase (GST) fusion proteins. GST fusion proteins were purified using glutathione-Sepharose 4B (GE Healthcare Bio-Sciences), according to the manufacturer's instruc- tions, and used for immunization to New Zealand White rabbits. Antigens were emulsified with Freund's complete or incomplete adjuvant (DIFCO, Detroit, MI, USA) and injected subcutaneously at intervals of 2 weeks. After the sixth injection, immunoglobulins specific to antigens were affinity-purified using synthetic peptide of 41-58 amino acid residues coupled to CNBr-activated Sepharose 4B (GE Healthcare Bio-Sciences)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4987" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

